Package gameClient

Class Agent

java.lang.Object
gameClient.Agent
public class Agent
extends java.lang.Object
This class represent an "agent" on our Pokemon game. Agent is object that can move on directed weighted graph, agent search for close pokemons and eat them. each agent have source node, destination node, current value, current speed, realtime position that represent by 3D points, Pokemon- the next pokemon that this agents will eat. list of pokemon - be use when there is 2 pokemon near to one agent. list of the path that represent each time the next node that this agent will go to. (implemented by queue).

    • time

      public long time​(directed_weighted_graph g, int tmp, java.lang.String activePokemons, java.util.List<Pokemon> poks) throws org.json.JSONException
      complex function that calculate the time until the agent will be enough close to next node or pokemon. it calculate the time by multiple of his speed, weight of relevant edge, and ratio (if it may eat pokemon). and maybe this move catch this an agent on middle of edge because other agent came to node or eat their pokemon.
      Parameters:
      g - - graph of game
      tmp - - indicator if this agents in node or edge
      activePokemons - - string at JSON format that bring information about pokemon in the game
      poks - - list of pokemon that on the graph
      Returns:
      minimum time that this agent need to wait until he be near to next node or pokemon.
      Throws:
      org.json.JSONException - -
